latestIgtvVideos.title: DIWALI LOOK BOOK✨
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I decided to restyle my old Diwali outfits in a way that they’re extra yet comfortable. 
I really went out of my comfort zone for this video and I hope you guys like it. 

Most of the outfits I’m wearing are tailor made. You can buy the cloth online and get it stitched or even purchase ready-made clothes online/ from a store. 

Outfit 1- Styled a blue silk saree from @nallisilksarees as a lehenga along with the top I bought from @hm  and earrings from @gemsinjewels_ 
Outfit 2- Paired a pink sharara and dupata with a scarf (used as a top) from @freequeindia. The jewellery set is very old but I’m sure you can find something similar online. 
Outfit 3- Paired a turtle neck top from @hm with a lehenga that I bought from Lajpat Nagar.

latestIgtvVideos.title: MENTAL HEALTH
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hey guys, 
I am so sorry about the delay but my instagram kept glitching yest so I couldn’t upload this vid. 
I edited out a lot of parts which I felt weren’t necessary. 
1) I have been feeling extremely frustrated and overwhelmed since the past 2-3 days and so I felt the need to go live yesterday and speak my heart out.
2) I have always talked about Mental Health and I will continue to do so. 
3) If you do not agree with what I’m saying and you have any VALID points that you’d like to share, My DMs are always open. If you’re just going to come here and abuse, I’ll block you without even thinking twice. 
3) I have mentioned several pages and websites towards the end of this video which provide online therapy/ counselling. So you guys can go and check them out. Two of them which I trust are @counselindia and @utsaah_psy but please suit yourself. 
4) Here are some accounts that I follow which talk about mental health, body positivity and several other things.  Some of them are: @farrhad @thepurplemusclestory @itsoktotalk @mentalhealthtalksindia @viceindia 
IT IS A TOUGH TIME FOR EACH AND EVERY ONE OF US. PLEASE BE KIND TO YOURSELF AND TO OTHERS. Practice what you preach. 🌈

latestIgtvVideos.title: 𝙇𝙀𝙏𝙏𝙀𝙍 𝙏𝙊 𝙈𝙔 𝘽𝙀𝙎𝙏 𝙁𝙍𝙄𝙀𝙉𝘿
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hello baby girl,
I just want to start off by saying that I know I can't sing for shit but I wanted to do something special for you to tell you how much I love and appreciate you. You asked me to play a song for you on my ukulele last night but I did that even before you asked me to. (It's photograph by Ed Sheeran)
Also, I wish I could be there with you right now to give you a tight hug and puchis but I can't do that so I'll save them for whenever we meet next.
I've told you about a thousand times how much you mean to me and I will tell you a million times more because it is never enough. My college life was what it was because of YOU. We might have the lowest attendance and our teachers might hate us but I wouldn't have it any other way. The memories we have made especially in these past 2 years mean the world to me. We have done EVERYTHING together from getting drunk and embarrassing ourselves, to taking coaching together (which we bunked half of the times), to going to north campus every week, going for career counseling, going to Satya Niketan and kailash colony, you coming over to my place 5 times a week (your second home), crying over boys together, buying the exact same clothes unintentionally and then even wearing them at the same time and the list is never-ending. I never thought that I would find someone who would mean this much to me. You are by far the most caring, beautiful, and kindest person I have ever met. People usually say that they're just one call away but you actually meant it. When I was at my lowest, you were the only person who was there for me, you let me cry on your shoulder for hours (and then you started crying because you can't see me cry). We started off as acquaintances, eventually became friends and now you're like the sister I never had, you're my family and I cannot imagine my life without you. College is getting over and we might not meet that often, or talk every day, hell we might end up miles away from each other but I know that whenever I do see you, you will come running to me and give me the tightest hug and say, "missed you chotu". THANK YOU FOR BEING YOU.
I love you. @lakshita_seth ❤️

latestIgtvVideos.title: EATING DISORDERS AND HOW TO LEAD A HEALTHY LIFESTYLE
latestIgtvVideos.caption: A huge thanks to @thesmithashetty for taking our time for this live session. Ma’am talks in detail about what Eating disorders are, types of eating disorders, their impact and the Habits you can inculcate to lead a healthy life! ❤️🌈. Eating Disorders are an example of how Mental Health can directly impact our Physical Health and vice versa. ✨

latestIgtvVideos.title: ANXIETY AND RELATED DISORDERS PT.1
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Heyy guys! I am sorry about this video being in two parts. I wish I could edit then but I cannot sooo ya. 
Anyway, a lot of you had several questions pertaining to anxiety, we tried answering most of them. Anxiety is one of the most common mental illnesses. We talk about the types of Anxiety Disorders, their causes, how to seek help and much more! 
A huge thanks to Dr Bobby Thakur from @counselindia for taking our time for this life session and for being extremely patient. If you guys have any other questions you can reach out to them on their instagram handle. 🥰

latestIgtvVideos.title: WHAT ARE MOOD DISORDERS? With Dr. Rahul Murada
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hey guys! Thank you for tuning in. Even though there were some connectivity issues I hope that we were able to answer most of your questions and you took away something from this session. 
A huge thanks to Dr @drrahulmurada for taking our time for this session even though he has a busy schedule. ✨
If you guys have any queries you can reach out to either of us.
MENTAL HEALTH IS IMPORTANT.
REACHING OUT IS IMPORTANT. SEEKING HELP IS IMPORTANT. 
It is OKAY to not feel OKAY. 
Sending lots of love and positive vibes to you all! ❤️

latestIgtvVideos.title: A lil pep up🥰
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hi guys, I woke up today feeling extremely low, I haven’t been okay lately and I have no shame in accepting it. I’ve had anxiety since a while now and some days are just not as good as others. There are days when I doubt myself and my capabilities but there are also days, like today where I choose to pick myself up. Soooo Here is a small video of me trying to cheer myself up in my night suit, all natural. 
Just know that it’s OKAY to NOT BE OKAY. It’s OKAY to take a little time off. It’s OKAY to be selfish sometimes and prioritise yourself and your mental health, the people who love and care for you will be there for you regardless. 
I know things are uncertain right now and you might feel like everything is falling apart, but you will get better. 
I hope that me doing whatever it is that I’m trying to do, brings a smile on your face.🌈
I might stay inactive on this account for a while now. If I don’t reply to your DMs, comments or anything just know that it’s nothing personal I still love and appreciate you but I need to put my mental health first right now. Thank you ❤️.
Song- life is crazy from wake up sid @shankarehsaanloy (this song ALWAYS cheers me up) (I don’t own any copyrights to this music)
